N2  - The article presents information on a study which used both strategic management and financial theory to explore the relationship between corporate diversification strategy and systematic or market risk. A discussion is presented about the measures selected for market power, capital intensity and financial leverage. Details related to sources of data used in the study and various risks associated with diversification in industry are presented. An overview of previous research on diversification risk is presented.
